		Title = "Connecting to Servers";
		Content = "<p>If you already know what server you want to use, Colloquy makes it very easy to connect! Just tap the \U201c+\U201d button on the Connections tab, select \U201cIRC Connection\U201d and enter the server address. You can tell Colloquy to automatically join rooms by adding them to the \U201cJoin Rooms\U201d list or to always connect to the network when Colloquy is opened. Under \U201cAdvanced\U201d, you can change things like the server port, specify SSL, and enter a password for your nickname or for the server.</p>";
		SectionHeader = Troubleshooting;
	},
	{
		Title = "Joining Chat Rooms";
		Content = "<p>There are a number of ways to join chat rooms in Colloquy! The first way is to type the room names into the \U201cJoin Rooms\U201d list when creating the connection. The second way to join a chat room is to tap the \U201c+\U201d button in the Colloquies tab, select \U201cJoin a Chat Room\U201d and enter the room name and tap \U201cJoin\U201d. If the room has password, you can enter it there. You can also type \U201c/join #room\U201d or tap on a room name in a chat to join the room. </p>";
