		Title = "Supported Commands";
		Content = "<ul>\n\t<li><strong>/amazon <em>[locale] search</em> - </strong>This will search for the item on Amazon. It will default to searching in whatever locale your device is set to, however you can specify a custom locale if you like. Locales are limited to Great Britain, Germany, China, Japan, France, Canada and United States.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/browser <em>[last] [site]</em> - </strong>Without any arguments, this will open up Colloquy\U2019s built in web browser. Typing \U201c/browser last\U201d will open the last website that you visited in Colloquy\U2019s browser. Typing \U201c/browser http://colloquy.mobi\U201d will open up the browser to the website specified, in this case, Colloquy\U2019s website.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/clear - </strong>This will remove all chat on screen.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/google <em>[locale] search</em> - </strong>Opens up a search with Google for your search terms. It will default to searching in whatever language your device is set to, however you can specify a custom language if you like.</li> \n\t<li><strong>/help - </strong>This will bring up the help screen you using now.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/list <em>[search]</em> - </strong>Open up a list of all the chat rooms on the server you are currently connected to.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/msg <em>user</em> - </strong>This will open a private message with the user specified.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/music <em>[next | previous | stop | play]</em> - </strong>Without any arguments, this will send the current song title, artist and album to the chat.</li> With one of the optional arguments, you can control your music from within Colloquy.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/join <em>#room</em> - </strong>This will join you to the room specified.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/search <em>query</em> - </strong>This will search on <u>SearchIRC.com</u> for a chat room that matches your string.\n\t<li><strong>/whois <em>user</em> - </strong>This will display information about the specified user.</li>\n\t<li><strong>/wikipedia <em>[locale] search</em> - </strong>Same as /google, only for Wikipedia.</li>\n</ul>";
